profile_positions.description:
Consultant and Researcher at the work fields water management and hydro communication.

Master thesis: a design guideline to reduce flood damage in regional water systems (successful). Specialist in hydraulic flood modelling (SOBEK1D2D) e.g.
■	Flood damage calculations with Dutch flood damage calculation module based on several flooding scenarios;
■	Development of flood damage reducing strategies for secondary embankments in relation to land use planning (e.g. Schiphol Airport); 
■	Precipitation monitoring with hydro software.

Data analysis of historical and measured observations (water levels, discharges, velocities, number of lock passages, precipitation, pumped discharges) of the Twente canals. Purpose of the analysis was to construct a water balance of the system. This was necessary for implementing a decision support system for operational sluice management (by order of Rijkswaterstaat Oost-Nederland).
